    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-14T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-14T12:00:00-05:00" n="394"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d394">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111A.R.–N.C./100: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-14T14:00:00-03:00"
                            >May 14, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>217. Department’s 123, May 13, 7 p.m. To the Under Secretary from Fenwick. Not
                    familiar with Podestá Costa’s views but other members discussing same problem. I
                    am in complete accord with Department’s views and will insist that if recess
                    taken Committee will be prepared to reassemble immediately upon call.</p>
                <p>Committee is considering on my initiative recommendation to governments of
                    American Republics that a collective protest be made against recent violation of
                    neutrality undermining whole basis of neutral rights and duties.<note n="74"
                        xml:id="d394fn1">See “Protest against the violation of neutrality of
                        Denmark, Norway, Holland, Belgium, and Luxemburg,” in <hi rend="italic"
                            >Minutes of the Sessions Held by the Inter-American Neutrality
                            Committee</hi>, Appendix A, Law and Treaty Series No. 15, p. 100.</note>
                    [Fenwick.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
